3. The base prime representation of 3 is [0, 1, 0, 0, 0, ...].
4. The base prime representation of 4 is [2, 0, 0, 0, 0, ...].
5. The base prime representation of 5 is [0, 0, 1, 0, 0, ...].
6. The base prime representation of 6 is [1, 1, 0, 0, 0, ...].
7. The base prime representation of 7 is [0, 0, 0, 1, 0, ...].
8. The base prime representation of 8 is [3, 0, 0, 0, 0, ...].

