The function \( j(x) = \sqrt{x - 1} \). Therefore, we need to find \( j(7) \):

\[
j(7) = \sqrt{7 - 1} = \sqrt{6}
\]

### Step 2: Find \( h(j(7)) \)

We already calculated \( j(7) = \sqrt{6} \), so next we need to find \( h(\sqrt{6}) \). The function \( h(x) = x^2 + 1 \):

\[
