\]

### Step 3: Determine \( j^{-1}(x) \) and find \( j^{-1}(7) \)

The function \( j(x) = \sqrt{x - 1} \) has an inverse \( j^{-1}(x) \). To find the inverse, we solve for \( x \) in terms of \( y \):

\[
