\[ A + 120 = 180 \]
\[ A = 180 - 120 \]
\[ A = 60 \]

Therefore, the measure of the first angle is 60 degrees. The second angle is:
\[ 90 - A = 90 - 60 = 30 \text{ degrees} \]

The third angle is:
\[ A + 30 = 60 + 30 = 90 \text{ degrees} \]

So, the measures of the angles are 60 degrees, 30 degrees, and 90 degrees. The smallest angle is 30 degrees.

