I0319 18:15:53.375439 125263652324928 reward_manager.py:164] completions:	 To determine how long it will take to fill the tank using both pipes, we need to calculate the combined rate at which the tank is filled by both pipes.

Pipe A fills the tank at a rate of 2 cubic meters per minute.
Pipe B fills the tank at a rate of 3 cubic meters per minute.

When both pipes are opened simultaneously, their rates add up:
\[ \text{Combined rate} = \text{Rate of Pipe A} + \text{Rate of Pipe B} \]
\[ \text{Combined rate} = 2 \text{ cubic meters/minute} + 3 \text{ cubic meters/minute} \]
\[ \text{Combined rate} = 5 \text{ cubic meters/minute} \]

Next, we need to find out how long it will take to fill the tank with a capacity of 120 cubic meters at this combined rate. This can be calculated using the formula:
\[ \text{Time} = \frac{\text{Total Capacity}}{\text{Combined Rate}} \]
\[ \text{Time} = \frac{120 \text{ cubic meters}}{5 \text{ cubic meters/minute}} \]
\[ \text{Time} = 24 \text{ minutes} \]

Therefore, it will take 24 minutes to fill the tank using both pipes simultaneously.
