\[ x - 3 = 8 \]
\[ x = 8 + 3 \]
\[ x = 11 \]

So, Alex bought 11 boxes. Now we can calculate how many boxes Tom bought:
\[ \text{Tom's boxes} = x + 4 = 11 + 4 = 15 \]

