   \[
   16 \text{ blocks} \times \frac{1}{8} \text{ miles/block} = 2 \text{ miles}
   \]

2. **Determine the time available before the ice cream melts**:
   The ice cream will melt in 10 minutes, which is equivalent to:
   \[
   \text{Time available} = 10 \text{ minutes} = \frac{10}{60} \text{ hours} = \frac{1}{6} \text{ hours}
   \]

3. **Calculate the required speed**:
   Jack needs to cover 2 miles in \(\frac{1}{6}\) of an hour. The required speed \(v\) (in miles per hour) is given by the formula:
   \[
   v = \frac{\text{Distance}}{\text{Time}} = \frac{2 \text{ miles}}{\frac{1}{6} \text{ hours}} = 2 \times 6 = 12 \text{ miles per hour}
   \]

Thus, Jack needs to jog at a speed of \(\boxed{12}\) miles per hour to get to the beach before his ice cream melts.
