The total measure of the interior angles of one regular pentagon is calculated by using the formula for the sum of the interior angles of a polygon, which is \((n-2) \times 180\) degrees, where \(n\) is the number of sides. For a pentagon (\(n=5\)), the sum of the interior angles is:

\[
(5-2) \times 180 = 3 \times 180 = 540 \text{ degrees}
\]

Since the gazebo has six sides, and each side is a regular pentagon, the total measure of all the interior angles of the gazebo is:

\[
6 \times 540 = 3240 \text{ degrees}
\]

Therefore, the total measure of all the interior angles of the gazebo is:

\[
\boxed{3240}
\]
