2. Add the pages she has already read to the pages she will read in the next 6 days.
3. Subtract the total number of pages she will have read from the total number of pages in the novel to find out how many pages she still needs to read.

Let's do this step-by-step using Python code.
```python
# Given values
total_pages = 472
pages_read_already = 187
pages_per_day = 25
days_to_read = 6

# Calculate the total number of pages she will read in the next 6 days
pages_to_read_next_6_days = pages_per_day * days_to_read

# Calculate the total number of pages she will have read after 6 days
total_pages_read = pages_read_already + pages_to_read_next_6_days

# Calculate the number of pages left to read
pages_left_to_read = total_pages - total_pages_read
print(pages_left_to_read)
```
