\[ a = 0.25, \quad b = -3.625, \quad c = 12.875, \quad d = -3.5. \]

So the polynomial is:
\[ p(x) = 0.25x^3 - 3.625x^2 + 12.875x - 3.5. \]

Using this polynomial, we find that:
\[ p(5) = 11.0. \]

Thus, the value of \( p(5) \) is \(\boxed{11}\).
