x2, y2 = -1, 2
x3, y3 = 0, -1

# Calculate the area using the formula
area = 0.5 * abs(x1*(y2 - y3) + x2*(y3 - y1) + x3*(y1 - y2))
print(area)
```
```output
2.0
```
The area of the triangle with vertices \((2, -3)\), \((-1, 2)\), and \((0, -1)\) is \(\boxed{2}\).
