Consider the 30-60-90 right triangle, where the sides are in the ratio \(1 : \sqrt{3} : 2\). In this triangle, the tangent of the angle opposite the side of length 1 is \(\frac{1}{\sqrt{3}}\). This angle is \(30^\circ\) or \(\frac{\pi}{6}\) radians.

Therefore, \(\arctan \frac{1}{\sqrt{3}} = \frac{\pi}{6}\).

Thus, the value is \(\boxed{\frac{\pi}{6}}\).
