```
The results show that for various values of \( x \) (specifically, \( x = 7k \) for \( k \) from 1 to 10), the remainder when \( p_1 + p_2 \) is divided by 7 is consistently 2.

Thus, the remainder when \( p_1 + p_2 \) is divided by 7 is \(\boxed{2}\).
