2. Using this equivalence, we can simplify the expression \(97^{40}\):
\[ 97^{40} \equiv (-1)^{40} \pmod{98} \]

3. Compute \((-1)^{40}\):
\[ (-1)^{40} = 1 \]

4. Therefore:
\[ 97^{40} \equiv 1 \pmod{98} \]

The remainder when \(97^{40}\) is divided by 98 is \(1\).

