I0319 20:26:05.053398 125263652324928 reward_manager.py:164] completions:	 To find the remainder when \(2007 \cdot 2008 \cdot 2009 \cdot 2010 \cdot 2011\) is divided by 23, we can first find the remainders of each of the individual numbers when divided by 23. Then we can multiply these remainders together and find the remainder of the product when divided by 23.

Here are the remainders of each number when divided by 23:
- \(2007 \mod 23\)
- \(2008 \mod 23\)
- \(2009 \mod 23\)
- \(2010 \mod 23\)
- \(2011 \mod 23\)

We can calculate these remainders as follows:

\[
2007 \div 23 = 87 \text{ remainder } 6 \implies 2007 \equiv 6 \pmod{23}
\]
\[
2008 \div 23 = 87 \text{ remainder } 7 \implies 2008 \equiv 7 \pmod{23}
\]
\[
2009 \div 23 = 87 \text{ remainder } 8 \implies 2009 \equiv 8 \pmod{23}
\]
\[
2010 \div 23 = 87 \text{ remainder } 9 \implies 2010 \equiv 9 \pmod{23}
\]
\[
2011 \div 23 = 87 \text{ remainder } 10 \implies 2011 \equiv 10 \pmod{23}
\]

So, we need to find the remainder when \(6 \cdot 7 \cdot 8 \cdot 9 \cdot 10\) is divided by 23.

We can calculate this step by step:

\[
6 \cdot 7 = 42 \equiv 6 \pmod{23}
\]
\[
6 \cdot 8 = 48 \equiv 6 \cdot 8 - 2 \cdot 23 = 6 \cdot 8 - 46 = 48 - 46 = 2 \pmod{23}
\]
\[
2 \cdot 9 = 18 \equiv 18 \pmod{23}
\]
\[
18 \cdot 10 = 180 \equiv 180 - 7 \cdot 23 = 180 - 161 = 19 \pmod{23}
\]

So, the remainder when \(2007 \cdot 2008 \cdot 2009 \cdot 2010 \cdot 2011\) is divided by 23 is 19. Let's verify this with Python code.
