1. **Calculate Lily's time to finish the race**:
   Lily runs at 20 meters per second. The race is 300 meters long.
   Time taken for Lily to finish the race = Distance / Speed = 300 meters / 20 meters per second = 15 seconds.

2. **Calculate how far Alex runs in the same time**:
   Alex runs at 22 meters per second.
   Distance Alex runs in 15 seconds = Speed × Time = 22 meters per second × 15 seconds = 330 meters.

3. **Determine how many meters ahead Alex is**:
   Since the race is 300 meters long, Alex will have run 330 meters when Lily finishes.
   Difference in distance = Distance Alex runs - Race distance = 330 meters - 300 meters = 30 meters.

Thus, Alex will be 30 meters ahead of Lily when Lily crosses the finish line.
