```
The smallest positive integer \(m\) such that \(\lambda^m\) has a nonnegative imaginary part is \(m = 1\). The smallest positive integer \(n > m\) such that \(\lambda^n\) has a nonnegative imaginary part is \(n = 3\). Therefore, the value of \(n - m\) is \(3 - 1 = 2\).

So, the final answer is \(\boxed{2}\).
