# Define the equation
equation = Eq((2*x)/3 - (x)/9, 1/6)

# Solve the equation
solution = solve(equation, x)
print(solution)
```
```output
[0.300000000000000]
```
The solution obtained from solving the equation using Python is \(x = 0.3\), which is equivalent to \(\frac{3}{10}\).

Therefore, the value of \(x\) that satisfies the equation \(\frac{2x}{3} - \frac{x}{9} = \frac{1}{6}\) is \(\boxed{\frac{3}{10}}\).
