\[ P(t) = P_0 \cdot 2^{t/3} \]
where \(P_0\) is the initial population and \(t\) is the time in months.

Given that the current population is 150 rabbits, we can express the population 4 years (48 months) ago as:
\[ P(48) = P_0 \cdot 2^{48/3} = P_0 \cdot 2^{16} \]

We need to find \(P_0\). Since 2 years ago (24 months) the population was 50% larger than it was 4 years ago (48 months), we can express the population 24 months ago as:
