\[
51817 \div 14641 = 3 \quad \text{(quotient)} \quad \text{so the coefficient of } 11^4 \text{ is 3.}
\]
We subtract \(14641 \cdot 3 = 43923\) from 51817 to get the remainder:
\[
51817 - 43923 = 7894.
\]

Next, we find how many times \(11^3 = 1331\) fits into 7894:
\[
7894 \div 1331 = 5 \quad \text{(quotient)} \quad \text{so the coefficient of } 11^3 \text{ is 5.}
\]
