   \[
   \frac{x^4}{x^2} = x^2
   \]
   Multiply \( x^2 \) by \( g(x) \):
   \[
   x^2 \cdot (x^2 + 2x + 1) = x^4 + 2x^3 + x^2
   \]
   Subtract this from \( f(x) \):
   \[
   (x^4 - 2x^3 + 5x^2 - 7x + 3) - (x^4 + 2x^3 + x^2) = -4x^3 + 4x^2 - 7x + 3
   \]

3. **Second Division Step:**
