   \]
   Subtract this from the current polynomial:
   \[
   (12x^2 - 3x + 3) - (12x^2 + 24x + 12) = -27x - 9
   \]

Since the degree of \(-27x - 9\) is less than the degree of \( x^2 + 2x + 1 \), the division process stops here. The remainder is:
\[
\boxed{-27x - 9}
