- After the first purchase, the discount is 10%, so the customer pays \(100 \times (1 - 0.10) = 100 \times 0.90 = 90\) dollars.
- After the second purchase, the discount is 20%, so the customer pays \(100 \times (1 - 0.20) = 100 \times 0.80 = 80\) dollars.
- After the third purchase, the discount is 30%, so the customer pays \(100 \times (1 - 0.30) = 100 \times 0.70 = 70\) dollars.

The total amount the customer pays after all discounts is the sum of the amounts after each discount. Let's use Python to calculate this.
