   - The number of possible sequences of 3 uppercase letters is \(26 \times 26 \times 26 = 26^3\).
   - The number of possible sequences of 3 lowercase letters is also \(26 \times 26 \times 26 = 26^3\).
   - Therefore, the total number of possible letter sequences (either all uppercase or all lowercase) is \(26^3 + 26^3 = 2 \times 26^3\).
   - There are 10 possible single-digit numbers (0 through 9), so the total number of possible passwords is \((2 \times 26^3) \times 10 = 20 \times 26^3\).

