   \text{Number of European coins} = 20\% \text{ of } 250 = 0.20 \times 250 = 50
   \]

2. Calculate the number of coins from South America:
   \[
   \text{Number of South American coins} = 30\% \text{ of } 250 = 0.30 \times 250 = 75
   \]

3. Calculate the number of coins from Africa by subtracting the number of European and South American coins from the total number of coins:
   \[
   \text{Number of African coins} = 250 - (\text{Number of European coins} + \text{Number of South American coins}) = 250 - (50 + 75) = 250 - 125 = 125
   \]

Thus, the number of African coins Lena has is \(\boxed{125}\).
