What is the range of $f+g$?
I0319 22:30:28.780195 125263652324928 reward_manager.py:164] completions:	 To determine the range of the function \( f + g \) where \( f \) and \( g \) are defined as described, we first need to identify the possible values of \( f(x) \) and \( g(x) \).

Given that \( f(x) \in A \) and \( g(x) \in B \) for all \( x \in A \cup B \), we know that:
\[ A = \{ x \mid -1 \le x \le 5 \} \]
\[ B = \{ x \mid 2 \le x \le 7 \} \]

The function \( f(x) \) can take any value in the interval \([-1, 5]\) and the function \( g(x) \) can take any value in the interval \([2, 7]\). The sum \( f(x) + g(x) \) will therefore be the sum of a value from \([-1, 5]\) and a value from \([2, 7]\).

To find the range of \( f + g \), we need to determine the minimum and maximum possible values of \( f(x) + g(x) \).

1. The minimum value of \( f(x) + g(x) \) occurs when \( f(x) \) is at its minimum and \( g(x) \) is at its minimum:
   \[ f(x) = -1 \quad \text{and} \quad g(x) = 2 \implies f(x) + g(x) = -1 + 2 = 1 \]

2. The maximum value of \( f(x) + g(x) \) occurs when \( f(x) \) is at its maximum and \( g(x) \) is at its maximum:
   \[ f(x) = 5 \quad \text{and} \quad g(x) = 7 \implies f(x) + g(x) = 5 + 7 = 12 \]

Since \( f(x) \) and \( g(x) \) can take any value within their respective intervals, \( f(x) + g(x) \) can take any value between the minimum and maximum values calculated above. Therefore, the range of \( f + g \) is:
\[ [1, 12] \]

Thus, the range of \( f + g \) is \(\boxed{[1, 12]}\).
