Subtract the distance Samantha skates from the distance Alexis travels:
\[ \text{Difference} = \text{Total Distance}_{\text{Alexis}} - \text{Distance}_{\text{Samantha}} \]
\[ \text{Difference} = 42 \text{ miles} - 32 \text{ miles} = 10 \text{ miles} \]

